com.gh.bmd.jrt.android.invocation

Class FilterContextInvocation<INPUT,OUTPUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gh.bmd.jrt.android.invocation.FilterContextInvocation<INPUT,OUTPUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    INPUT - the input data type.
    OUTPUT - the output data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ContextInvocation<INPUT,OUTPUT>, ContextInvocationFactory<INPUT,OUTPUT>, Invocation<INPUT,OUTPUT>, InvocationFactory<INPUT,OUTPUT>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PassingContextInvocation

    public abstract class FilterContextInvocation<INPUT,OUTPUT>
extends Object
implements ContextInvocation<INPUT,OUTPUT>, ContextInvocationFactory<INPUT,OUTPUT>
    Abstract implementation of an invocation filtering each input and transforming it in output data.

    Note that the implementing class must not retain an internal variable state.

    Created by davide on 5/2/15.
